# Git commits (Tomodict)

This repository belongs to the **personal** GitHub account **kaizerfcm**.

## Before any commit or push

1. Verify identity:
   ```bash
   git config user.name
   git config user.email
   ```
2. **Do not commit or push** if:
   - `user.name` or `user.email` indicates the work account **fmorais-plana** (or any `@plana` / work email the user has flagged)
   - identity is unknown or not the personal account
3. Stop and tell the user to switch Git credentials to **kaizerfcm** / personal email before proceeding.

## Allowed committer

- **kaizerfcm** with personal email (e.g. `felipecastanheiramorais@gmail.com`)

## Never

- Run `git config` to change user.name or user.email in this repo
- Commit on behalf of fmorais-plana or any work identity
- Force-push to `main` unless the user explicitly requests it
